frus:attachment.p:
Having examined the proceedings had in the matter of the demand presented by
                        his excellency the American ambassador for the extradition of Charles Kratz,
                        for the crime of bribery committed in the city of St. Louis, Mo.;

It appearing that said extradition was asked for as a matter of reciprocity
                        by virtue of our law upon the question, and not upon ihe basis of the
                        existing treaty between Mexico and the United States of America;
